assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: JSS Corporation engages in the operation of a sports club in Japan. The company plans, operates, and manages sports clubs, such as swimming schools, tennis schools, and fitness clubs; sells, repairs, and maintains sports equipment and accessories, and equipment; processes machines and equipment; holds, plans, manages, and operates cram school classes, sports classes, culture classes, and health promotion classes; and develops and sells computers, software, and terminal equipment. It is involved in the construction work business, building design, civil engineering, steel structure, plumbing, and machinery installation and design works; real estate rental business; sale of processed metal product and machinery, health equipment, beauty equipment, and medical equipment; marketing business, such as research, analysis, and consulting related to the market and advertisement; planning, production, manufacturing, leasing, distribution, sales, and import/export of audio/visual software, such as music tapes, video tapes, compact discs, and DVDs; and worker dispatch business. In addition, the company sells and exports clothing, food, cosmetics, books, stationeries, toys, quasi-drugs, hygiene products, daily necessities, and accessories; offers security, maintenance inspection, and cleaning services for internal and external incidental facilities of various buildings, as well as health checkups and guidance services. Further, it manages restaurants; buys and sells antiques; and plans and implements various events, seminars, workshops, etc. The company was formerly known as Japan Swimming Service Co., Ltd. and changed its name to JSS Corporation in June 1991. JSS Corporation was incorporated in 1976 and is based in Osaka, Japan.
